# .doc-contract — declares every tracked markdown surface (ADR 0005, dotfiles).
# Asserted in CI by scripts/check-doc-truth.sh. First tier match wins.
#   LIVING     — updated as a side effect of merges; must stay true
#   GENERATED  — produced or asserted by CI/scripts
#   SOURCE     — markdown-as-config (atom content, templates)
#   HISTORICAL — point-in-time records; banner required, never updated

# Original build packet — frozen 2026-05-18; ISA.md is the canonical spec.
HISTORICAL spec/*.md

LIVING README.md
LIVING CHANGELOG.md
LIVING CONTRIBUTING.md
LIVING SECURITY.md
LIVING CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
LIVING CLAUDE.md
LIVING STATUS.md
LIVING ISA.md
LIVING Plans/*.md
LIVING docs/*.md
LIVING packages/*/README.md

# Pack atom content is config, not prose — adapters compile it verbatim.
SOURCE examples/*/atoms/*.md
LIVING examples/*/README.md
SOURCE .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md
# Test-fixture markdown is config-as-test-data (importer inputs, sample packs),
# not prose surfaces — exempt from LIVING currency + checkbox rules.
SOURCE packages/*/tests/fixtures/*

# Open work lives in GitHub issues, never as doc checkboxes.
BANNED:LIVING,GENERATED ^[[:space:]]*[-*] \[ \]
# CLI was renamed workgraph -> agentpack in v0.5.1; "Workgraph" the separate
# product is still legitimate, so only CLI invocations are banned.
BANNED workgraph (install|add|remove|plan|apply|validate|pack|publish|inspect|audit|verify|history|uninstall|rollback|login|init)
